description:
&lt;p&gt;We are looking to recruit an enthusiastic and flexible individual to undertake the role of APA to support our Heads of Nursing in Medicine and Emergency Care.  The post is offered on 31.5 hours per week to be worked over 4 days which will need to include working on a Thursday and Friday, other days of work can be discussed at interview.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;The successful candidate will ideally possess RSA II, or equivalent, and have proven secretarial and time management skills.  Previous medical secretarial experience will be advantageous.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Duties will include:&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Providing secretarial support to the Heads of Nursing in Medicine and Emergency Care, including cover for leave/absence of Divisional PA&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Dealing with all telephone enquiries&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Managing Diaries by liaising with others, within and across Divisions and externally&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Be fully conversant with all required electronic systems for correspondence&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;General administration duties (e.g. filing, copying, collecting notes)&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Maintain systems and processes to establish and maintain effective communication and confidentiality of information&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Assistant the Heads of Nursing/PA to ensure that lessons are learnt from issues arising from risk reports/complaints etc.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Ideally you will have some NHS experience and possess good IT skills.  The ideal candidate must possess good oral and written communication skills.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Good people and clerical skills are essential to this post and an applicant would have to display good interpersonal skills at interview&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Interviews to be held on 26th November 2020 on Microsoft Teams.&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
